{
  "texts": [
    "Weak evaluation can damage trust in these tools and limit their usefulness (8).",
    "Poor or shallow validation can lead to unreliable models, misleading public health findings, wrong policy decisions, and eventually a decline in trust in sentiment analysis for public health.",
    "A main concern found in the literature is the overuse of standard metrics without enough understanding of when and how they should be used.",
    "Metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score are often reported (24) (25) (26) 34).",
    "Our review (Figure 4) also shows that accuracy is the most common metric."
  ]
}